# README  conventions

`README.md` is the **public-facing entry point** for the repo. Keep it in **English** only.

## Language

- Write all headings, body text, and table content in English
- Do not add Japanese sections or bilingual blocks

## Do not include in README

The following belong elsewhere (Cursor rules, internal docs, or future decisions)—not in README:

- **Host install policy** … e.g. “do not run pip/npm on the host” (see `no-local-env-pollution.mdc`)
- **Planned extensions / roadmap** … e.g. TiDB, GCS, IAP backlog items
- **Links to `docs/`** … whether `docs/` is tracked in git is undecided; do not link or index doc files from README

## Do include in README

- Prerequisites and how to run locally / prod-like / deploy
- Tech stack and directory layout (high level)
- URLs, health check, and essential behavior notes
- Inline command examples (copy-paste ready)

## Example

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
ローカル開発は Docker Compose を使う。ホストへの pip install は禁止。
See [requirements](./docs/01_app_requirements.md).

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
Local development uses **Docker Compose**.
To enable IAP, configure IAP in the console first, then use `--no-allow-unauthenticated --iap`.
```
